<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HUBS, BEARINGS, AND SEALS (NON-DRIVE AXLES) - INSTALLATION (WHEEL BEARINGS - OIL LUBRICATED)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl0200206">
        <title>INSTALLATION (WHEEL BEARINGS - OIL LUBRICATED)</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Prelubricate inner and outer bearings with a coating of recommended oil bearing lube as
                        described in
                        <hotlnk document="s02002s_19.xml" xrefid="hl0200201">LUBRICATION.</hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Assemble bearings and seal as described in section
                        <hotlnk document="s02002s_13.xml" xrefid="hl0200202">INSTALL SEALS.</hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Adjust bearings. For bearing adjustment, refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s02002s_6.xml" xrefid="hl0200203">WHEEL BEARING ADJUSTMENT.</hotlnk>
                        Install the hub cap and fill hub to a level that is up to but not to exceed 5/16 inch above the
                        MIN lube line as shown on window face of hub cap.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>For aluminum type hub caps, apply sealant to the threads on the fill plug before installing.
                        With rubber plug type hub caps, be sure that the rubber plug is seated. Wipe excess lubricant
                        from hub cap which could appear as a leaking cap after vehicle operation. On hub caps that are
                        made of composite materials, tighten the fill screw to 20 in-lbs. (2.3 N&#183;m)
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>For grease lubricated bearings, refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s02002s_19.xml" xrefid="hl0200201">LUBRICATION.</hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
